# Copy to app/.env.local and fill in. `make dev` auto-generates app/.env.local
# pointing at the local validator, so you only need this file for devnet / manual
# setups.

# ─── Cluster RPC ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local validator by default (what `make dev` uses).
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899
# For devnet, point at the public devnet RPC instead:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com

# ─── Meridian program ID ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Matches the deployed program / IDL address (same id on localnet + devnet).
NEXT_PUBLIC_PROGRAM_ID=6oe2PzNoWyLMrWHqGAj5hirRUX68z35oqBTW9T1E9mWX

# ─── USDC mint ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Not configured here. The app reads the USDC mint from the on-chain Config
# account (fetchConfig → c.usdcMint) — the single source of truth, set when the
# program was initialized. There is deliberately no NEXT_PUBLIC_USDC_MINT: a
# build-time value would only drift from on-chain.

# ─── Pyth Hermes endpoint (live prices) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Hermes serves the MAG7 equity price feeds used for live UI prices (and, in
# later units, oracle settlement). The Landing + Markets pages poll it via the
# `usePrices` hook. The public endpoint is moving to an API-key model
# (mid-2026); treat it as configurable. Leave unset to use the default
# (https://hermes.pyth.network) baked into app/src/lib/prices.ts.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_HERMES_URL=https://hermes.pyth.network

# ─── Dashboard "Market insights" chat (Claude) ──────────────────────────────
# SERVER-SIDE key (NOT exposed to the browser) for the /api/insights route that
# powers the "Ask about any market" chat. When set, the chat answers free-form
# questions via Claude, grounded in the live market data. When UNSET, the chat
# gracefully falls back to a deterministic on-chain market lookup (no key
# needed). Optional model override (default claude-haiku-4-5-20251001).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001

# ─── Read-only demo wallet (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────
# A real account's public key (no signing). When set and no wallet is connected,
# the dashboard's activity heatmap + portfolio chart show THIS account's live
# on-chain data instead of an empty state. `make dev` can point this at the
# local admin so a logged-out dashboard isn't blank.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_WALLET=
